<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 04 at 5:04PM CDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Bradley
and southeastern Hamilton Counties through 645 PM EDT...
At 603 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
South Cleveland, or near Cleveland, moving northwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Cleveland, Soddy-Daisy, Lakesite, South Cleveland,
Harrison, East Cleveland, Wildwood Lake, Collegedale and Waterville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
